bio:
Justin Langseth is the Vice President of Data Sharing Business Development at Snowflake. Before joining Snowflake, Justin co-founded Zoomdata in 2012. Previously, he co-founded and was CTO of Claraview (sold to Teradata in 2008) and then Clarabridge (spun off from Claraview). Prior to Claraview, he was co-founder and CTO of Strategy.com, a former real-time data monetization and insights subsidiary of MicroStrategy. He is the lead inventor on 16 granted technology patents related to data monetization, data personalization, and real-time, unstructured, and big data. He graduated from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology where he received a SB in Management of Information Technology from the MIT Sloan School of Management.
